Uses of Package
com.shc.ahttp.client.response

  • Packages that use com.shc.ahttp.client.response 
    Package Description
    com.shc.ahttp.client
    This package provides clients for making HTTP calls, with support for message converters which can be used to marshal and unmarshal code before and after the HTTP call in a generic way.
    com.shc.ahttp.client.request
    This class provides the generic request classes for various HTTP operations such as GET, POST using Apache HTTP Client API.
    com.shc.ahttp.client.response
    The package encapsulates all response related classes that could possibly be returned from the HTTP client call
  • Classes in com.shc.ahttp.client.response used by com.shc.ahttp.client 
    Class and Description
    SClientResponse
    This class provides an extra field for storing the parsed response object along with all the fields from AHttpClientResponse to represent the state and content of the response returned from a successful HTTP client call.
  • Classes in com.shc.ahttp.client.response used by com.shc.ahttp.client.request 
    Class and Description
    AHttpClientResponse
    This class provides all the fields required to represent the state and content of the response returned from a successful HTTP client call.
  • Classes in com.shc.ahttp.client.response used by com.shc.ahttp.client.response 
    Class and Description
    AHttpClientResponse
    This class provides all the fields required to represent the state and content of the response returned from a successful HTTP client call.
